author: Michael Janda
title: More than 700,000 Australians lost their jobs in first week of COVID-19 shutdown
description: The COVID-19 pandemic resulted in a 5.5 per cent slump in jobs in the first week after extensive business shutdowns and social-distancing limits were introduced to contain the virus, new ABS figures show.
